<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<package xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xmlns:xsd="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema">
  <metadata>
    <id>calibre</id>
    <title>Calibre</title>
    <version>1.16.0</version>
    <authors>Kovid Goyal</authors>
    <owners>Gary Ewan Park</owners>
    <summary>calibre is the one stop solution to all your e-book needs.</summary>
    <description>calibre is a free and open source e-book library management application developed by users of e-books for users of e-books.</description>
    <projectUrl>http://calibre-ebook.com/</projectUrl>
    <tags>ebook library management</tags>
    <copyright>Kovid Goyal</copyright>
    <licenseUrl>http://www.gnu.org/licenses/gpl.html</licenseUrl>
    <requireLicenseAcceptance>false</requireLicenseAcceptance>
    <iconUrl>https://github.com/gep13/ChocolateyPackages/raw/master/calibre/calibre.png</iconUrl>
    <releaseNotes>
    - New: Add a tool to browse all images in the book with their thumbnails. Useful for visually locating an image. To launch it, use View->Browse images in book.
    - New: Allow creation of new, empty books via File->Create new book
    - New: Add buttons to easily create formatting such as bold/italic/colors/etc. when editing HTML files
    - New: Add button to easily insert <img> tag while editing HTML
    - New: Add options to change the default font families/sizes for the preview panel
    - New: Allow customizing which dockable windows occupy the four dock corners via Edit->Preferences. You can now also choose to have more than one row of windows in a given dock area.
    - Fixed: When editing AZW3 files with no images in them, do not incorrectly display a number of binary records from the AZW3 file as 'unknown' miscellaneous files
    - Fixed: Fix marking image as cover not working for AZW3 files if the file did not previously have a cover
    - Fixed: AZW3 Output: Do not refuse to create the ToC if it has only a single entry
    - Fixed: Fix crashes when processing some books that contain malformed markup on OS X and windows 64bit machines
    - Fixed: Fix error when renaming the html file currently displayed in the preview panel and that file is not the file being currently edited
    - Fixed: Fix crash when editing books that have links to absolute paths.
    - Fixed: Fix book not being marked as modified after editing the ToC
    - Fixed: When syncing the position of the preview panel to the cursor in the editor and the cursor is at or before the <body> tag set the position of the preview panel to the top of the file, so that the top margin of the body tag is seen easily.
    - Fixed: Fix trying to import an html file/css file via the add new file button always resulting in a blank file
    - Fixed: Fix replacing a file with another file with exactly the same filename causing an error.
    - Fixed: Have the ToC view refresh itself after any major operation on the book
    - Fixed: Fix pasting in the image editor not working
    </releaseNotes>
  </metadata>
</package>
